  "prompt": "Do Apple employees get discounts?",
  "response": "Yes, Apple employees typically receive various discounts on Apple products and services. These perks can include:\n\n1. **Employee Purchase Program (EPP)**: Employees can often purchase Apple products at a discount. This might include a percentage off the retail price for items like iPhones, iPads, MacBooks, and other hardware.\n\n2. **Friends and Family Discounts**: Employees sometimes have the ability to extend discounts to friends and family members, often through special purchase programs.\n\n3. **Employee Stock Purchase Plan (ESPP)**: Apple has a program that allows eligible employees to purchase company stock at a discounted rate.\n\n4. **Education and Professional Development**: Discounts on courses and professional development tools are also common within many corporations, including Apple.\n\n5. **Variety of Other Benefits**: Apple employees may also have access to other benefits and discounts on various services and goods, wellness programs, and more, which can sometimes include third-party products and services.\n\nIt's important to note that the specific details and availability of discounts and benefits can vary depending on factors such as the employee's role, location, and length of service. Employees should refer to their internal resources or HR department for the most accurate and detailed information.",
